The article is a presidential proclamation issued by Barack Obama on September 25, 2009, recognizing Gold Star Mother's and Families' Day. The proclamation honors the sacrifices made by military servicemembers and acknowledges the profound loss and sorrow experienced by the families they leave behind. Gold Star Mothers and Families, who have lost loved ones in service to the country, are praised for their strength and dedication to helping other military families cope with their loss. The proclamation calls on government officials to display the flag of the United States on this special day and encourages the American people to do the same as a public expression of sympathy and respect for Gold Star Mothers and Families.